com.yworks.yfiles.view

Class ViewportLimiter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.yworks.yfiles.view.ViewportLimiter

  • public class ViewportLimiter
extends Object
    Helper class used by CanvasControl to limit the interactive movement of the viewport.

    The ViewportLimiter instance should be consulted whenever the user tries to change the viewport. Using method limitViewport(CanvasControl, RectD) the desired viewport can be validated by the implementation. Note that setting the Zoom property or ViewPoint property will not be influenced by implementations of this class. It is up to the caller to perform verification.

    See Also:
    getBounds()

      • getCurrentBounds

        protected RectD getCurrentBounds(CanvasControl canvas,
                                 RectD suggestedViewport)
        Gets the to bounds that should be honored for the upcoming call.

        This method is used as callback by limitViewport(CanvasControl, RectD) for each request. The default implementation just yields Bounds.

        Parameters:
        canvas - The canvas control.
        suggestedViewport - The suggested viewport.
        Returns:
        The bounds to honor or null.
